# Model Library workstream

Read `.cursor/plans/HANDOFF-model-library.md` before starting work. Git workflow: `.cursor/plans/AGENT-GIT-INSTRUCTIONS.md`.

## Branch and repos

- Monorepo: `REBUS-Industries/prism` — branch **`feat/model-library`** only
- API polyrepo: **`REBUS-Industries/prism-models-service`** — feature branches off `main`
- Bootstrap: `scaffold/prism-models-service/` if polyrepo not created yet
- Daily sync: `git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main`

## Owned files (edit freely)

- `web/src/admin/pages/Model*.vue`, `Models.vue`, `PrismModelLibrary.vue`
- `web/src/admin/components/Model*.vue`, `web/src/admin/utils/model*.ts`
- `prism-models-service/src/**`
- `docs/MODEL_LIBRARY.md`

## Do not edit

- Fixture builder files (`Fixture*.vue`, `fixtureAssembly.ts`, `prism-fixtures-service`)
- Materials editor files (`Material*.vue`, `server/src/materials/**`)
- `prism/server/**` except `server/src/api/keys.ts` for `models:*` scopes

## Shared files — coordinate before merge

- `web/src/shared/api.ts` — add `modelsApi` at end; announce in team chat
- `web/src/admin/App.vue` — nav/routes; announce first

## Build and deploy (keep UI + API in sync)

- Pre-PR: `cd web && npm run build`
- **Web only:** `gh workflow run web-image --repo REBUS-Industries/prism --ref feat/model-library`
- **Models API:** merge `prism-models-service` PR; `models-image` on merge to `main`, or:
  `gh workflow run models-image --repo REBUS-Industries/prism-models-service --ref <branch>`
- Merge via `/prism-merge <PR#>` or `/prism-merge prism-models-service#N`
- Dev: https://prism-dev.rebus.industries

## Commit format

`feat|fix|chore(web): <description>` (models-service: `feat:` / `fix:` without web scope)
